President Donald Trump has received a report from Deputy Secretary of Defense Shanahan that fulfills the mandate of Executive Order 13806. This report is the most comprehensive assessment of the manufacturing and defense industrial base in American history. The President is taking action to protect the health and stability of the defense industrial base and its supply chains. The Secretaries of Defense, Commerce, Energy, and Labor are implementing the report's recommendations to address vulnerabilities. The Trump Administration is focused on rebuilding the military and revitalizing American manufacturing through increased defense spending, modernization initiatives, and economic policies that prioritize national security.